@startuml C4_Pattern_SimpleTask
!include https://raw.githubusercontent.com/plantuml-stdlib/C4-PlantUML/master/C4_Component.puml

title YAWL Workflow Pattern - Simple Task Execution

Boundary(user, "User") {
    Actor(user_actor, "User")
}

Boundary(yawl_system, "YAWL Engine") {
    Component(ynet_runner, "YNetRunner", "Orchestrator", "Workflow executor")
    Component(task_mgr, "TaskManager", "Task handler", "Lifecycle mgmt")
    Component(executor_pool, "ExecutorPool", "Virtual threads", "Task execution")
    Component(persistence, "Persistence", "Database", "State storage")
}

Boundary(external, "External") {
    Component(worklist_ui, "Worklist UI", "User interface", "Task listing")
    Component(task_form, "Task Form", "Data capture", "User input")
}

user_actor --> worklist_ui: Accesses
worklist_ui --> ynet_runner: Queries tasks
ynet_runner --> task_mgr: Retrieves available

task_mgr --> persistence: Loads task
persistence --> worklist_ui: Returns task list

user_actor --> task_form: Claims & executes task
task_form --> ynet_runner: Submits completion

ynet_runner --> executor_pool: Executes post-tasks
executor_pool --> ynet_runner: Returns outcome

ynet_runner --> persistence: Persists state
persistence --> worklist_ui: Updates task list

Note as N1
Sequence: Create → Allocate → Claim → Execute → Complete
Actors: User, YNetRunner, Database
Timing: Synchronous API calls
End note

SHOW_LEGEND()
@enduml
